    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-22T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-22T13:00:00-05:00" n="373"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d373">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/674</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-22T18:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 22, 1918, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 24, 9.50 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3001. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1"
                        >Sheldon</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 1723. Referring to your No. 1444, Department’s 2279, October 18, 5 p.m.
                    Before signing this undertaking I think I should call your attention to my
                    letter of June 18 [<hi rend="italic">September 19</hi>], No. 5418,<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d373fn1">Not printed.</note> second page, under caption of purchase
                    of 2,000,000 tons. I think it is important to have an understanding as to
                    whether subsequent sales of iron ore should apply (1) in relief proportionately
                    of the engagement of the three Associated Governments or (2) to relieve the
                    share in the total liability of say one of the Associated Governments who might
                    purchase for their own account or make a sale. I am awaiting signing the
                    undertakings, text of which was telegraphed, until the foregoing point is
                    cleared up.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Laughlin</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
